Magnesium is one of the most chemically active metals due to its low reduction potential [117, 120]. Table 3 shows the position and potential of Mg in contrast to Zn, Fe and Ag, materials that have been used previously for clinical applications, compared to the standard hydrogen electrode. Therefore, magnesium is widely used as the main element in sacrificial anode coatings to protect other metals from corrosion [121–123].Table 3
